<span id="Uploaded_&amp;_favorited_worlds"></span>
== 업로드 & 즐겨찾기한 월드 ==

[[Special:MyLanguage/Social#Actions|상호작용]] 하단에는 유저가 업로드한 월드 목록과 공개로 설정된 즐겨찾기 월드 목록이 표시됩니다<br />이 목록은 추가된 날짜, 최근 업데이트, 이름, 최근 사용 순으로 정렬할 수 있습니다.

<span id="Short_links"></span>
=== 단축 링크 ===

유저 프로필은 VRChat의 <code>vrch.at</code> 단축 링크 도메인과 유저 ID를 조합하여 공유할 수 있습니다.<br />예를 들어 <code><nowiki>https://vrch.at/<userId></nowiki></code>와 같은 식입니다. 이 링크를 이용하면 VRChat 웹사이트의 사용자 프로필 페이지(<code><nowiki>https://vrchat.com/home/user/<userId></nowiki></code>)로 연결됩니다.

<span id="Social_menu"></span>
=== 소셜 메뉴 ===

[[File:Social Menu.webp|thumb|alt=VRChat 메인 메뉴의 소셜 탭 이미지입니다.|<span lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">The social tab of the main menu in VRChat.</span>]]

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
===Friend Locations===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
'''Friend Locations''' includes a list of friends who are available on "Online" (green) status, or "Join Me" (blue) statuses, and are present in an accessible world such as Public, Friends+, Friends, Group Public, Group+ instances. Below these available users will also display a list of all Friends currently online in Private Instances.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
===Group Activity===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
'''Group Activity''' includes a list of available [[Special:MyLanguage/Groups|Group]] instances, for Groups that you have joined. Creating a Group, Group+, or Group Public instance, if you have the ability, will result in it appearing on the Group Activity tab for users in that group.
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
===All Friends===
</div>

 
<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
'''All Friends''' shows the entire list of your friends who are currently online, including Friends on "Ask Me" (orange) or "Do Not Disturb" (red) statuses. It also shows your friends active on the website or friends that are currently offline.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
===In Instance===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
'''In Instance''' displays each user who is currently present in the instance you are in; users who have you blocked, while still inside of the instance with you may not appear on this tab, unless you are a Host or a [[Special:MyLanguage/Groups|Group]] Instance Moderator. The "Here" tab on the Quick Menu functions the same as this row.
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
===Favorite Friends===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
'''Favorite Friends''' lists are three rows of friends who you have chosen to 'Favorite'. It can be placed in one of the three rows. Each list can be renamed to help with organization.
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
===Recently Seen===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
'''Recently Seen''' users are other users you've met in instances. Up to the last 100 recently seen users can be found in this tab and are ordered from the most recent to the oldest.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
===Blocked===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
'''Blocked''' users are other users who you decided to block. They can be clicked upon in this tab, and unblocked if desired.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Friends==
</div>

{{Stub|Add quirks that have to do with friends and such.}}
<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Friends on VRChat are other users that you trust, it acts much like how friending users on other platforms work, you can see whenever that user is online or on the website, send and receive invites from them, and add notes to them. Friends inside of your instance will have their name appear in yellow, and will also have their rank appear in yellow with a (Friend) indicator.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Mutuals==
<!-- Do we want a feature infobox? -->
{{Infobox/Feature
|name=Mutuals
|image=
|platforms= PC, Android, iOS
|branch_live_date = December 3, 2025
|branch_live_version = 2025.4.2
|branch_live_releasenote = [https://docs.vrchat.com/docs/vrchat-202542 2025.4.2]
|branch_openbeta_date = November 10, 2025
|branch_openbeta_version = 2025.4.2 Build 1761
|branch_openbeta_releasenote = [https://docs.vrchat.com/docs/vrchat-202542-openbeta 2025.4.2 Open Beta]
}}
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Mutuals are a feature that allows the user to view mutual friends or groups of other users.
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
There are two ways to see mutuals, in the Quick Menu or the Main Menu with a button "Show X Mutuals". In the Quick Menu, the button can be found on top of user actions. In the Main Menu, the button will be found on the top right, next to the report button.
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
If you wish to prevent other users from seeing your mutual friends and groups or appearing as so for others, you can turn off "Show Mutual Connections" in the '''Comfort & Safety''' section of your settings in the Main Menu. Doing so will change the text of the button from "Show X Mutuals" to "No Known Mutuals". Additionally, your user icon will be hidden, and your username will appear as "Hidden Mutual" when you appear in the mutuals in one of your friends.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Discord Friends==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Seen in the Social tab under "All Friends", this feature allows you to see your Discord friends with their current status and to perform different actions. Friends with a Discord account linked will have a Discord icon displayed on their profile
</div> 

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
If your friend has linked their Discord account to their VRChat account, you will be able to invite them to join your instance through Discord. Otherwise, you will be able to invite them to create a VRChat account. You or your friends may prevent your VRChat account from being shown in the Discord section by turning off the "Allow Discord Friends" setting in the '''Comfort & Safety''' section of the settings.
</div>

